<%# ENSAYO RULES AND FAQs
Two ways to embed ruby code in html
1. < % % >: this will just run the code inside  
2. < %= % >: this will run the code plus it prints the result in html

note:
  1. Always use double quote when doing string interpolation
    YES: "Hello #{target}" NO: 'Hello #{target}'
    see below for example:
  2. You can also a block of code within a single tag
    - This is useful if you just want to run a block of codes
    < %=
      3.times do |n|
        puts n
      end
    % >
  3. and you also run a block of codes with multiple < % % > tags.
    - This is useful if you want to run a block of codes and at the same time
      output the some result of it using html tags.
      < % 3.times do |n| % >
        <p>< %= n % ></p>
      < % end % >

%>
